The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Airport trio

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, April 7: Three passengers were detained at Calcutta airport today for allegedly assaulting a senior official of Indian after the flight got delayed by three hours.

 Prabir Bhattacharya, 52, a resident of south Calcutta, and two of his companions were booked on an Indian flight to Mumbai, from where they were to fly to New York. 

 The flight, IC 273, was scheduled to take off from Netaji Subhas Chandra Bose International Airport at 6.30 pm. It got delayed by three hours due to technical problems, a spokesperson for Indian said.

 Around 8 pm, Bhattacharya went up to the Indian official and demanded to know why the flight was late. An argument started, during which Bhattacharya assaulted the official, his colleagues alleged. 




